OUTRIDER INFORMATION

1. The cargo/tech bay has room for additional elements to adapt the Outrider to specific roles.

2. You can place up to three extra M containers along the spine of the ship, centered on X=0.0, at an altitude of Z=10.0. After placement be sure to link them to the container hub, located on the ceiling above the entryway.

3. You can place a Shield Generator M at coordinates X=0.0, Y=-7.0, Z=2.0

4. You can place a Rocket Fuel Tank M inside the tech bay and a Rocket Engine M outside in the socket between the atmo engines.

5. You can even wedge a single territory scanner in there, lengthwise or vertical. I don't have placaement coords for that.

6. The L space engines can be easily replaced. When placing the new engines, aim at the yellow and black placement marker at the rear of the engine housing, flip the engine to the proper orientation, and sink it in with the precision move keys to coordinates X=+/-20.0, Y=-45.5, Z=3.0

7. The atmo engines can be easily replaced as well. Aim at their yellow and black placement marker and use the precision move keys to shift it to coordinates X=+/-8.5, Y=-42.5, Z=3.0

8. There is a slot for a warp drive in the entry area. To place the warp drive, aim at their yellow and black placement marker - no precision key movement necessary. Proper coordinates are X=0.0, Y=-8.0, Z=1.0. After placement, link the cargo hub to the warp drive and rerun an autoconfig for your flight script on the hover seat controller.

9. In the cubby forward of the cargo bay there is a XS container for emergency scrap and a programming board with an exclusive script created by RobRocketpants: FOX Status Report, which provides key info about your ship and activates an augmented reality display of damaged elements, allowing for easier repairs.

10. The Outrider BP comes with an additional BP called 'Outrider Paint Tool.' To repaint your Outrider, simply gather the materials and spawn the tool(don't swap the materials, use the designated materials), select a desired hull section from the BP(grab it by the matching colored voxel handles), copy it, enter build mode on the Outrider, press Ctrl+V to bring up the copied section, double click a new material in your inventory, and use precision mode to paste the resulting shape into the proper position on your ship(DON'T HOLD SHIFT WHEN PASTING). Don't forget to delete the little voxel handles from your ship after you paste.

11. The Outrider comes with FOX HUD pre-installed. For operation instructions, visit TobiwanKenobi's PvP guide and find the link to the FOX HUD manual.


Thank you for buying my cool internet spaceship with your space dollars. If you have additional questions, contact @Tobi-wan Kenobi#2452 on Discord.
